{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce mandatory licensing for professional carers in England",
        "additional_details": "Professional carers support elderly, disabled and vulnerable people with medication, personal care and safeguarding, often inside private homes without supervision.\r\n\r\nCare agencies are regulated by the CQC, but individual carers in England are not nationally licensed like nurses, doctors or security staff. I have seen firsthand how inconsistent care can affect vulnerable people and families.\r\n\r\nCarers should have mandatory training, DBS checks and accountability through a licensing system.",
        "background": "Create a national licensing and professional registration system for carers and domiciliary care workers who provide personal care, safeguarding support and assistance to elderly, disabled and vulnerable people across England.",
